<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7855> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7855" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "quaestor in 48 or 47 (MRR 2.274, 285, note 4), is most probably P. Appuleius (15). Tr. pl. in 43 (MRR 2.339; see Sumner, Phoenix 25, 1971, 361-363).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5801> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5801" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 47, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5741> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5741" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proquaestor in Asia (Cic. Fam. 13.45, and 46; see 48, Quaestors, and note 4), probably before the governorship of Servilius Isauricus (see 46, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5638> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5638" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "4 Appuleius could possibly be identified with M. Appuleius (RE no. 13), Quaestor in 44, or Sex. Appuleius (no. 17), or P. Appuleius (no. 15). Syme bases his identification on the resemblance of these letters of Cicero to those concerning Quintius Gallus (Fam. 13.43, and 44) and Marcius Philippus (Fam. 13.73, and 74). See 47, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5637> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5637" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably a Quaestor this year in Asia Minor under Domitius Calvinus (Cic. Fam. 13.45, and 46; see Syme, A nat. Stud. Buckler 315-317)." .
